Total U.S. aluminum stocks held byintegrated and non-integrated producers and smelters includingscrap, ingot, metal in process and finished products rose to2,470,000 short tons in December from 2,451,000 short tons inNovember, American Bureau Metal Statistics said.    Primary production rose to 278,000 tons in December from263,000 tons in November. Imports for consumption declined to114,000 tons in December from 150,000 tons in November.    Net shipments eased to 605,000 tons in December from608,000 tons in November. Ingot shipments were 87,000 tonsversus 99,000 tons, mill products shipments were 435,000 tonsversus 420,000 tons and casting shipments were 83,000 versus89,000. Reuter&#3;